author: Ubisoft
description:
Operation Tenfold Pursuit is coming to Rainbow Six Siege X on December 2 and delivering a free Operator rework for Thatcher. Thatcher will have his EMP grenades replaced with the E.G.S. Disruptor, a gadget that can detect the Defenders’ electronic devices through any surface, and then fire an electromagnetic pulse to temporarily knock them out. The new season will also introduce a new weapon — the PMR90A2 DMR — for Thatcher, Capitão, Nøkk, and Hibana; this new DMR will be exclusive to the Operation Tenfold Pursuit Premium Battle Pass for two weeks, after which it will be accessible to all players. 

Operation Tenfold Pursuit is also delivering a big balancing update for hard breaches and select Defenders. The Fortress map will be fully reworked, modernized, and ready for Ranked, with Skyscraper and Theme Park getting  modernized as well. title: This is Team Rainbow's last mission.

author: Ubisoft
description:
Team Rainbow is deployed to intercept Phobos' explosives. This is their last chance, their last mission, and they will see it through, no matter what.

About Rainbow Six Siege X:
Rainbow Six Siege X is an exciting, new approach to the first-person shooter experience that puts tactical combat and masterful destruction at the center of the action. Lead your team of unique operators through tense and thrilling combat scenarios, and achieve victory through smart preparation and strategic improvisation. Rainbow Six Siege X is available now on Xbox, PlayStation® and PC.
